Using the provided HTML structure, create a CSS file (styles.css) to style the "My Favorite Books" page. Your task is to apply styles using element selectors, classes, and IDs. Follow these requirements:

Style the body:
Use a sans-serif font
Set a background color


Style the header:
Add a background color
Center the text
Set the text color to white


Style the main headings (h1 and h2):
Choose appropriate colors
Adjust the font size if needed


Style the unordered lists:
Remove bullet points
Add some spacing between list items


Style individual list items:
Add a background color
Add some padding
Round the corners


Use the "bestseller" class to:
Make the text bold
Change the text color to make it stand out


Use IDs to style the fiction and non-fiction sections differently:
Add different background colors
Add padding
Round the corners


Style the footer:
Center the text
Make it italic


Use the "student-name" class to:
Make the text bold
Change the text color




